==English==

===Noun===
'''muffin'''

# a type of pastry
# {{baseball}} {{slang}} an 1800s baseball term meaning a less-talented player
# ''computer term'' a mechanism used in the Java Network Launching Protocol analogous to the [[cookie]] mechanism and which permits a program running in a [[browser]] to perform operations on a client machine

====Quotations====
''computer term''
*'''2001''': The name/value pairs provided by the PersistenceService are similar to browser cookies. The Java Web Start implementation honors this legacy by naming the pairs "'''muffins'''." &mdash; ''JNLP and Java Web Start'', Sun Developer Network, Technical Articles and Tips, 30 May 2001.

